						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the central shrine in the Vṛishabhapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Rājarāja I. Year 26: 1010-11 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription contains portions of the <hi rend="italic">praśasti, Tirumagaḷ pōla</hi> etc., of Rājarāja I.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record an endowment of sheep for a perpetual lamp by a <hi rend="italic">vāṇiyaṉ</hi> of Tañjāvūr. It also seems to record another endowment for a perpetual lamp.</p>						

						</summary>
